5.Counting Sort Algorithm :
ğŸ‘‰ Counting Sort ek non-comparison based sorting algorithm hai. Yeh algorithm elements ko count karke sort karta hai.
Matlab har number kitni baar aya hai, woh count karte hain, fir us count ko use karke final sorted array banate hain.
- Isme compare nahi karna padta, balki frequency count calculate hoti hai.
- Counting sort tab fast hota hai jab array ke numbers 0 to k range me ho (k bahut bada na ho).
- bahut bada array, negative numbers ke liye ye sorting kam nhi krta.
Example:
List: 4, 2, 2, 1, 3
Range = 0 to 4
Step 1: Count frequency
0 â†’ 0
1 â†’ 1
2 â†’ 2
3 â†’ 1
4 â†’ 1
Step 2: According to counts, final sorted array:
1, 2, 2, 3, 4
âš™ï¸ Steps to Implement Counting Sort :
                                1ï¸âƒ£ Find the maximum element â†’
                                                Because counting array ka size hum maximum element ke according banate hain.
                                                         Example:
                                                         arr = {4, 2, 2, 1, 3}
                                                         max = 4
                                2ï¸âƒ£ Create a count array â†’
                                                         Size = max + 1
                                                         Initialize all to zero. in java by default all are zero don't need extra work
                                                         Example:
                                                         count[0..4] = {0, 0, 0, 0, 0}
                                3ï¸âƒ£ Count occurrences of each number â†’
                                                Har element ke liye: count[arr[i]] = count[arr[i]]+1;
                                                After counting:  count = {0,1,2,1,1}
                                4ï¸âƒ£ Build the sorted output using count â†’
                                                Jitni baar koi number aaya hai, utni baar output me add karo.
                                                         Example:
                                                         1 â†’ 1 time
                                                         2 â†’ 2 times
                                                         3 â†’ 1 time
                                                         4 â†’ 1 time
                                                         Final: 1, 2, 2, 3, 4
                                                   intialize k = 0; 
                                                   for (int i=0; i<countArray.length; i++){
                                                      for (int j=0; j<countArray[i]; j++){ 
                                                             arr[k++]=i;}}
                                                         ye ya fir output array create kr lo.
                                5ï¸âƒ£ Copy back to original array â†’
                                                print original array
                                6ï¸âƒ£ Result â†’
                                             Array sorted in ascending order without comparisons. Final Output: 1, 2, 2, 3, 4
â±ï¸ Time Complexity:
Counting Sort = O(n + k)
Where:
n = number of elements
k = maximum value in array
